Italian Wins Title of Monte Carlo Rally 
Piero Liatti of Italy drove his Suburu Impreza to clinch the title of
the Monte Carlo auto rally after the fourth and final day on Wednesday.
The race is the first of this season's series and the victory will
definitely boost Liatti's confidence in the later races of the season.
Liatti beat two-time world champion Carlos Sainz of Spain to the second
place. Sainz was 55 seconds behind Liatti while current world champion
Tommi Makinen of Finland came home third with two minutes and 31
seconds behind.
The final day of the race featured a total of six stages with 125
kilometers.
